sdp/runner.log:2078:{"type":"tool_result","timestamp":"2026-04-25T19:44:09.641Z","tool_id":"run_shell_command_1777146249360_0","status":"success","output":"diff --git a/sdp/implementation-plan.md b/sdp/implementation-plan.md\nindex 4ed6434..5a9b512 100644\n--- a/sdp/implementation-plan.md\n+++ b/sdp/implementation-plan.md\n@@ -1,9 +1,9 @@\n-# PRD: CypherClaw Humanization — Structured Expression Rendering Layer — Implementation Plan\n+# PRD: CypherClaw Sampler — Granular Memory Voice as Primary Instrument — Implementation Plan\n \n-**Generated:** 2026-04-16T18:19:25.335643+00:00\n+**Generated:** 2026-04-25T18:39:59.551260+00:00\n **Source:** PRD v1.0\n-**Total tasks:** 40\n-**Estimated effort:** ~129 hours\n+**Total tasks:** 33\n+**Estimated effort:** ~111 hours\n \n ---\n \n@@ -15,16 +15,16 @@ Sprints are sequential. Tasks within a sprint can run in parallel unless a depen\n \n **Depends on:** Sprint 0 (Versioning System)\n \n-- **T-001** [T1] Build a rule-ablation debugger that re-renders a score with selected rules disabled to localize expressive problems. (~3h)\n-- **T-002** [T1] Build the RenderPass framework: ordered rule stack with stable order, per-rule enable flags, per-rule quantity k, and role-filter gating. (~3h)\n-- **T-003** [T1] Implement R1 Metric Accent: per-beat-position velocity multiplier applied only to non-grid-locked melodic/accent voices. (~3h)\n-- **T-004** [T1] Implement R2 Phrase Arch (Todd/KTH): parabolic tempo + loudness arch over each phrase, modulated by section envelope. (~3h)\n-- **T-005** [T1] Implement R3 Agogic Accent: lengthen + emphasize notes at local contour apex or harmonic-charge peak. (~3h)\n-- **T-006** [T1] Implement R4 Duration Contrast: exaggerate short-vs-long by log(dur_ratio_to_median), melodic roles only, capped at ±10%. (~3h)\n-- **T-007** [T1] Implement R5 Final Ritardando: Friberg–Sundberg square-root tempo curve over last 20–30% of cadential phrases. (~3h)\n-- **T-008** [T1] Implement R6 Punctuation + Breath: lengthen terminal note at phrase boundary and insert breath silence of breath_after_ms. (~3h)\n-- **T-009** [T1] Implement R7 Articulation Shaping: per-note gate-time by style (legato 0.95–1.02, normal 0.7–0.85, staccato 0.3–0.5, staccatissimo 0.15–0.25) with contour adjustments. (~3h)\n-- **T-010** [T1] Implement R8 Microtiming Polish: per-note Gaussian jitter σ=3 ms on melodic, 1 ms on ostinato, 0 ms on grid-locked machine voices. (~3h)\n+- **T-001** [T1] Implement buffer-management protocol: `OnSamplerLoad(record)` allocates scsynth buffer + reads WAV; `OnSamplerFree` releases buffer; LRU eviction at 64-buffer cap. (~3h)\n+- **T-002** [T1] Implement `sampler_effects.scd` dedicated effects-bus SynthDef chain: long delay (1/4 to 1/2 measure), convolution reverb (FreeVerb fallback if no IR loaded), spectral freeze (PV_Freeze), comb-resonance tuned to B fundamental (61.74 Hz). (~3h)\n+- **T-003** [T1] Implement `sampler_dispatch.py` that converts a `(SampleRecord, PerformanceIntent, params)` tuple into the OSC bundle (`/s_new sw_sampler ...` + buffer-pool acquire) and ships it to scsynth. (~3h)\n+- **T-004** [T1] Per-voice gate-controlled lifecycle: composer can `play_sampler(record, duration_sec)` for fire-and-forget OR `start_sampler(record) -> handle; stop_sampler(handle)` for sustained voices. (~3h)\n+- **T-005** [T1] Integrate sampler effects bus into `master_bus.py` mix slot with appropriate gain staging (peak-normalized, not RMS) and post-mix compression bypass to preserve grain transients. (~3h)\n+- **T-006** [T1] Implement `sample_capture_daemon.py` rolling 60-second buffers reading from `system:capture_1` (contact mic) and `system:capture_2` (room mic) via JACK. (~3h)\n+- **T-007** [T1] Implement interesting-moment detector: novelty (spectral flux) + transient density + RMS thresholds + duration-min/max gating. (~3h)\n+- **T-008** [T1] Auto-tag captured samples: arc phase, mood, presence, time-of-day, plus heuristic acoustic tags (warm if low spectral centroid, metallic if high+narrow band, transient if high transient density, etc.). (~3h)\n+- **T-009** [T1] Captured samples land in `samples/contact/` or `samples/room/` as 24-bit 48 kHz WAV with metadata-tagged filename and an entry in `index.sqlite`. (~3h)\n+- **T-010** [T1] Implement self-quotation loop: when a song completes with arc-payoff > threshold AND clicks=0, sample a 4-second window of `SuperCollider:out_1` for the next session. (~3h)\n \n *Subtotal: ~30 hours*\n \n@@ -32,47 +32,42 @@ Sprints are sequential. Tasks within a sprint can run in parallel unless a depen\n \n **Depends on:** Sprint 0 (Versioning System), Sprint 1 (Quality Scoring)\n \n-- **T-011** [T1] Implement R12 Sensor-to-Intent Aggregation Matrix: smoothed IIR + hysteresis → aggregate intentions (global_energy, global_restraint, global_brightness). (~3h) → deps: T-001\n-- **T-012** [T1] Implement bounded reactive delta track in scheduler with per-parameter modulation caps. (~3h) → deps: T-001\n-- **T-013** [T1] Expose aggregate-intention telemetry (global_energy/restraint/brightness) in operator diagnostics, never raw one-to-one mappings. (~3h) → deps: T-001\n-- **T-014** [T1] Build the metric battery: IOI CoV, velocity σ, DNVR/DNODR, pitch-class entropy H1, Grooving Similarity (GS), tempo autocorrelation ρ₁, LZ76 compression ratio, novelty peaks per phrase, silence-at-phrase-boundaries. (~3h) → deps: T-001\n-- **T-015** [T1] Build anti-pattern tests: quantization ghosting, dynamic compression, motif ossification, random-as-expression (Ljung-Box), symmetric-arc uncanny, dead-silence failure. (~3h) → deps: T-001\n-- **T-016** [T1] Implement performance-worm logger: 2D trajectory in tempo–loudness space + convex-hull area computation as CI artifact. (~3h) → deps: T-001\n-- **T-017** [T1] Integrate metric battery + anti-pattern detectors into CI gate with fail-on-regression policy. (~3h) → deps: T-001\n-- **T-018** [T1] Embed rule-stack provenance in exported audio metadata (e.g., WAV iXML chunk or sidecar JSON) for listener-review workflow. (~3h) → deps: T-001\n+- **T-011** [T1] Implement anti-pattern detectors: `sampler_dominating` (sampler event count > 0.6 × total events) and `sampler_silent_quintet_member` (sampler used in <5% of last 50 pieces, mode-weighted). (~3h) → deps: T-001\n+- **T-012** [T1] End-to-end smoke test on cypherclaw: capture a known room sound, watch the composer self-quote it within 3 pieces, verify the self-listener observes the resulting peaks. (~3h) → deps: T-001\n+- **T-013** [T2] Update `docs/cypherclaw-musicianship-roadmap.md` to reflect the quintet, document the sampler architecture in `docs/cypherclaw-sampler-architecture.md`, and add a one-page artistic-intent doc `docs/cypherclaw-sampler-artistic-intent.md`. (~6h) → deps: T-001\n \n-*Subtotal: ~24 hours*\n+*Subtotal: ~12 hours*\n \n ### Sprint 3: Improvement Engine Hardening\n \n **Depends on:** Sprint 0 (Versioning System), Sprint 2 (Improvement Engine Hardening)\n \n-- **T-019** [T1] Enforce role-filter gating across R1–R8 with a single shared contract; verify machine identity preservation end-to-end. (~3h) → deps: T-011\n-- **T-020** [T1] Integrate partitura for phrase-feature extraction: harmonic_charge, melodic_charge, metric_weight, cadential detection, contour apex. (~3h) → deps: T-011\n-- **T-021** [T1] Implement R9 Motif Memory: LRU cache of motif hashes with variation menu and return-home decay. (~3h) → deps: T-011\n-- **T-022** [T1] Implement R10 Silence Budget: per-voice and per-section accumulators enforced at phrase boundaries. (~3h) → deps: T-011\n-- **T-023** [T1] Implement wind/voice lung-capacity constraints: 4–8 s continuous-play cap per instrument-sim voice. (~3h) → deps: T-011\n-- **T-024** [T1] Implement R11 Call-Response Gating: follower phrase intent complements leader's realized performance. (~3h) → deps: T-011\n-- **T-025** [T1] Compose SectionEnvelope with phrase arcs multiplicatively so section-level tempo elasticity modulates phrase-level shaping. (~3h) → deps: T-011\n-- **T-026** [T1] Implement tempo-dependent swing curve per Friberg/Sundström (3.5:1 at slow tempi down toward 1:1 at fast), with short-note near-constant ~100 ms. (~3h) → deps: T-011\n-- **T-027** [T1] Add arc-shape variety so not every phrase uses a symmetric parabola: per-phrase random selection from parabolic/cosine/asymmetric-Bezier/flat/inverted with peak-position variance. (~3h) → deps: T-011\n-- **T-028** [T1] Implement restraint parameter enforced as global dampener across rules. (~3h) → deps: T-011\n+- **T-014** [T2] Add systemd unit `cypherclaw-sample-capture.service` that runs `sample_capture_daemon.py` with `Restart=always`, dependent on `cypherclaw-jack.service`. (~6h) → deps: T-011\n+- **T-015** [T1] Implement TDD-grade test fixtures with canned 1-second audio windows representing each detector branch (silence, footsteps, dishwasher, music, dogs, transient cluster) for fast deterministic CI. (~3h) → deps: T-011\n+- **T-016** [T1] Wire `SampleSelector` into `cast_planner.select_cast_ids` so when the cast includes `sw_sampler`, a sample is pre-selected for the piece and attached to the cast metadata. (~3h) → deps: T-011\n+- **T-017** [T1] Per-mode sampler density gates: composer plays `floor(sampler_density * total_phrases) + Bernoulli(sampler_density)` sampler events per piece (clamped 0..total). (~3h) → deps: T-011\n+- **T-018** [T1] When a human plays the MIDI keyboard or Theramini for >5 seconds during a song, capture that input phrase to `samples/keyboard/` or `samples/theramini/` with full tagging. (~3h) → deps: T-011\n+- **T-019** [T1] Sample-aware harmonic planning: when a sample with known `pitch_hz` is selected, transpose to fit the current piece's key by computing the closest in-key root and applying `pitch_transpose_semitones`. (~3h) → deps: T-011\n+- **T-020** [T1] Add per-mode effects-bus presets: solitary/evening favor more reverb + delay; working_ambience uses minimal effects; storm uses high freeze + heavy comb-B. (~3h) → deps: T-011\n+- **T-021** [T2] Surface \"currently sampling X\" + \"playing sample Y from source Z\" in `operator_diagnostics.py` and the face/inkplate display. (~6h) → deps: T-011\n+- **T-022** [T1] Composer post-piece hook: write a sample-usage journal entry per piece (which samples played, what transformations, what arc payoff). (~3h) → deps: T-011\n+- **T-023** [T1] Implement `metrics::sampler_event_count_per_piece` and `metrics::sampler_library_vs_self_ratio` for the metrics-CI gate. (~3h) → deps: T-011\n \n-*Subtotal: ~30 hours*\n+*Subtotal: ~36 hours*\n \n ### Sprint 5: Library & CRUD Polish\n \n **Depends on:** Sprint 0 (Versioning System), Sprint 1 (Quality Scoring)\n \n-- **T-029** [T1] Implement the Event dataclass with score-level, performance-level, reactive-delta, and provenance fields. (~3h) → deps: T-001\n-- **T-030** [T1] Implement PerformanceIntent per-phrase metadata with arc shape, deviation bounds, tension target, restraint, and call/response role. (~3h) → deps: T-001\n-- **T-031** [T1] Implement SectionEnvelope with breakpoint functions over tempo_base, density_target, dynamic_plane, brightness, tension_trajectory. (~3h) → deps: T-001\n-- **T-032** [T1] Define IntentTag enum (build/settle/question/answer/withhold/punctuate) and require every phrase to carry one. (~3h) → deps: T-001\n-- **T-033** [T1] Define Role enum (ostinato/melody/pad/perc/accent/silence) with grid_locked flag and role-filter policy used by all rules. (~3h) → deps: T-001\n-- **T-034** [T1] Implement seeded-RNG architecture with per-stage sub-seeds derived from a root seed along a seed_path tuple. (~3h) → deps: T-001\n-- **T-035** [T1] Refactor composition stage to emit score-tree with PerformanceIntent + SectionEnvelope + IntentTag metadata, deterministic from composition seed. (~3h) → deps: T-001\n-- **T-036** [T1] Define the OSC/SuperCollider event contract that carries full Event metadata including rule_stack provenance through to the synth. (~3h) → deps: T-001\n-- **T-037** [T1] Build a deterministic replay harness that reproduces any past performance from (score, composition_seed, interpretation_seed, delta_track). (~3h) → deps: T-001\n+- **T-024** [T1] Define `SampleRecord` dataclass with sample-id, path, source, character tags, pitch, duration, captured-at, arc context, RMS, peak, transient density. (~3h) → deps: T-001\n+- **T-025** [T1] Define controlled `CHARACTER_TAGS` vocabulary (warm, metallic, wind, pulse, voice, mechanical, water, sustained, transient, percussive, harmonic, noisy). (~3h) → deps: T-001\n+- **T-026** [T1] Implement `SampleLibrary` on-disk store backed by `index.sqlite` with tag/source/pitch/mood-range queries. (~3h) → deps: T-001\n+- **T-027** [T1] Define on-disk directory layout under `/home/user/cypherclaw-data/samples/` with `library/`, `self/`, `room/`, `contact/`, `theramini/`, `keyboard/` subdirs and `index.sqlite`. (~3h) → deps: T-001\n+- **T-028** [T1] Implement `SampleSelector` mood/mode/arc-aware picker with deterministic seed-based selection within match set. (~3h) → deps: T-001\n+- **T-029** [T1] Add `sw_sampler` to `SIGNATURE_VOICES` quintet in `artist_identity.py` and update `VOICE_ROLES` so a `\"sampler\"` role maps to `\"sw_sampler\"`. (~3h) → deps: T-001\n+- **T-030** [T1] Add `sampler_density` field (0.0–1.0) to `ArtistMode` with mode-specific values: solitary 0.7, companion 0.25, working_ambience 0.10, evening_reflection 0.65, storm 0.45. (~3h) → deps: T-001\n+- **T-031** [T1] Register `voice_sampler` character in `character_registry.py` with `voice.synth = \"sw_sampler\"`, `voice.role = \"sampler\"`, default register, and per-mode gain overrides. (~3h) → deps: T-001\n+- **T-032** [T1] Implement `sw_sampler.scd` granular SynthDef with bufnum, grain-size, density, position-scrub, pitch-transpose, attack/release envelope, and effects-bus send. (~3h) → deps: T-001\n \n *Subtotal: ~27 hours*\n \n@@ -80,18 +75,16 @@ Sprints are sequential. Tasks within a sprint can run in parallel unless a depen\n \n **Depends on:** Sprint 0 (Versioning System)\n \n-- **T-038** [T2] Couple narrative engine to SectionEnvelope selection so dramatic arcs drive section choice. (~6h)\n-- **T-039** [T2] Build audio-rendered SSM + Foote novelty cross-check via librosa on the actual rendered audio. (~6h)\n-- **T-040** [T2] Establish listener-review workflow: weekly rendered pieces tagged with rule-stack provenance, ablation tooling documented for operators, review log template in place. (~6h)\n+- **T-033** [T2] Migrate Anthony's existing recorded music + handpicked field recordings into `samples/library/` with appropriate metadata. (~6h)\n \n-*Subtotal: ~18 hours*\n+*Subtotal: ~6 hours*\n \n ---\n \n ## Requirements Coverage\n \n-- **MUST requirements:** 37/37 covered\n-- **SHOULD requirements:** 3 included as stretch\n+- **MUST requirements:** 32/32 covered\n+- **SHOULD requirements:** 1 included as stretch\n \n **✓ All MUST requirements covered.**\n \ndiff --git a/sdp/task-graph.md b/sdp/task-graph.md\nindex 541f6b7..f7cc1bc 100644\n--- a/sdp/task-graph.md\n+++ b/sdp/task-graph.md\n@@ -1,8 +1,8 @@\n-# PRD: CypherClaw Humanization — Structured Expression Rendering Layer — Task Graph\n+# PRD: CypherClaw Sampler — Granular Memory Voice as Primary Instrument — Task Graph\n \n-**Generated:** 2026-04-16T18:19:25.335643+00:00\n-**Total tasks:** 40\n-**Estimated effort:** ~129 hours\n+**Generated:** 2026-04-25T18:39:59.551260+00:00\n+**Total tasks:** 33\n+**Estimated effort:** ~111 hours\n \n ---\n \n@@ -10,16 +10,16 @@\n \n | Order | Task ID | Description | Tier | Complexity | Est (hrs) | Reqs | Deps | Criteria |\n |-------|---------|-------------|------|------------|-----------|------|------|----------|\n-| 1 | T-001 | Build a rule-ablation debugger that re-renders a score with selected rules disabled to localize expressive problems. | T1 | 5 | 3 | CCH-010 | — | - CLI or Python API `ablate(score, seeds, disabled_rules=[...])` returns alternate PerformedPart<br/>- output includes a diff report showing which Event fields changed vs. full-stack render<br/>- tests cover single-rule ablation, pair ablation, and all-rules-off (should equal bit-identical Phase-1 baseline) |\n-| 2 | T-002 | Build the RenderPass framework: ordered rule stack with stable order, per-rule enable flags, per-rule quantity k, and role-filter gating. | T1 | 4 | 3 | CCH-011 | — | - `render/pass_.py` defines RenderPass(rules, enabled_flags, quantities) with apply(score_tree, seeds) → PerformedPart<br/>- rule order is fixed and documented: R1→R2→R3→R4→R5→R6→R7→R8→R9→R10→R11→R12<br/>- per-rule k defaults to 1.0; authoring surface exposes overrides per-piece and per-intent-tag<br/>- tests verify stable order, k=0 equals rule-disabled, k=1 equals calibrated default |\n-| 3 | T-003 | Implement R1 Metric Accent: per-beat-position velocity multiplier applied only to non-grid-locked melodic/accent voices. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-012 | — | - `render/rules/metric_accent.py` applies 16-step 4/4 table [1.00, 0.82, 0.92, 0.80, 0.95, 0.80, 0.90, 0.78, 0.97, 0.80, 0.91, 0.78, 0.94, 0.80, 0.90, 0.78] with meter-aware extension to 3/4, 6/8, 5/4, 7/8<br/>- rule skips ostinato + perc by role filter<br/>- tests verify velocity distribution matches table on 4/4 melodic passage and is unchanged on ostinato |\n-| 4 | T-004 | Implement R2 Phrase Arch (Todd/KTH): parabolic tempo + loudness arch over each phrase, modulated by section envelope. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-013 | — | - `render/rules/phrase_arch.py` computes tempo_mult(x) = 1 + k·(-4·(x-peak)² + 1)·tempo_deviation_pct/100 and matching amp_mult for normalized phrase position x<br/>- defaults: tempo_deviation_pct=4, peak=0.6, k=1.0<br/>- arc_shape parameter supports parabolic, cosine, asymmetric-Bezier, flat, inverted variants<br/>- composes multiplicatively with SectionEnvelope.tempo_base at each event<br/>- tests verify arc shape, peak position, and multiplicative composition |\n-| 5 | T-005 | Implement R3 Agogic Accent: lengthen + emphasize notes at local contour apex or harmonic-charge peak. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-014 | — | - `render/rules/agogic.py` detects contour apex (up-down peak) and harmonic_charge peak per phrase<br/>- at apex: duration multiplied by 1.05–1.15, velocity +3–6 dB<br/>- only one apex accent per phrase to avoid caricature<br/>- tests verify apex detection, magnitude, and one-per-phrase rule |\n-| 6 | T-006 | Implement R4 Duration Contrast: exaggerate short-vs-long by log(dur_ratio_to_median), melodic roles only, capped at ±10%. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-015 | — | - `render/rules/duration_contrast.py` applies log-scaled multiplier within [0.90, 1.10] on melodic voices<br/>- ostinato / perc skipped<br/>- tests verify short notes shortened, long notes lengthened, and cap enforcement |\n-| 7 | T-007 | Implement R5 Final Ritardando: Friberg–Sundberg square-root tempo curve over last 20–30% of cadential phrases. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-016 | — | - `render/rules/final_rit.py` applies tempo(x) = v₀·√(1 - α·(x-x_start)/(x_end-x_start)) for cadential phrases only<br/>- α default 0.35, onset position default 0.75 of phrase length<br/>- triggered only when is_cadential=True on phrase<br/>- tests verify curve shape, onset position, and non-application on non-cadential phrases |\n-| 8 | T-008 | Implement R6 Punctuation + Breath: lengthen terminal note at phrase boundary and insert breath silence of breath_after_ms. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-017 | — | - `render/rules/punctuation.py` multiplies terminal-note duration by 1.15–1.40 and inserts breath drawn from Gauss(breath_after_ms, 0.1·breath_after_ms)<br/>- breath counts against R10 silence budget<br/>- tests verify terminal-note extension, breath insertion, and budget accounting |\n-| 9 | T-009 | Implement R7 Articulation Shaping: per-note gate-time by style (legato 0.95–1.02, normal 0.7–0.85, staccato 0.3–0.5, staccatissimo 0.15–0.25) with contour adjustments. | T1 | 5 | 3 | CCH-018 | — | - `render/rules/articulation.py` sets dur_sec as gate_time × nominal<br/>- repeated-pitch notes slightly shorter (×0.92); notes after upward leaps slightly longer (×1.05)<br/>- tests verify gate-time range per style and contour adjustments |\n-| 10 | T-010 | Implement R8 Microtiming Polish: per-note Gaussian jitter σ=3 ms on melodic, 1 ms on ostinato, 0 ms on grid-locked machine voices. | T1 | 4 | 3 | CCH-019 | — | - `render/rules/microtiming.py` is the ONLY place white noise enters the pipeline<br/>- σ values below listener JND (10 ms) by design<br/>- grid-locked voices receive σ=0 and emerge with timing_deviation_ms==0<br/>- tests verify σ by role and zero-jitter on grid-locked |\n+| 1 | T-001 | Implement buffer-management protocol: `OnSamplerLoad(record)` allocates scsynth buffer + reads WAV; `OnSamplerFree` releases buffer; LRU eviction at 64-buffer cap. | T1 | 4 | 3 | CCS-010 | — | - `tools/senseweave/sampler_buffers.py` exposes `BufferPool(scsynth_client, capacity=64)` with `acquire(record) -> bufnum`, `release(record)`, `evict_lru()`<br/>- WAV file path → `/b_allocRead bufnum path 0 -1` over OSC<br/>- LRU eviction triggered automatically when `acquire` exceeds capacity<br/>- on scsynth restart, pool detects buffer-id reuse failure and rebuilds<br/>- tests with a mock OSC client verify allocate, evict, release, and reuse paths |\n+| 2 | T-002 | Implement `sampler_effects.scd` dedicated effects-bus SynthDef chain: long delay (1/4 to 1/2 measure), convolution reverb (FreeVerb fallback if no IR loaded), spectral freeze (PV_Freeze), comb-resonance tuned to B fundamental (61.74 Hz). | T1 | 5 | 3 | CCS-011 | — | - SynthDef `sw_sampler_fx` reads from a stereo bus and writes to master bus<br/>- args: `delay_time` (sec, default 0.5), `delay_feedback` (0..0.85, default 0.55), `verb_mix` (default 0.35), `room_size` (default 0.7), `freeze_amount` (0..1, default 0.0), `comb_b_amount` (0..1, default 0.25), `comb_b_freq` (default 61.74)<br/>- bus number conventionally 16 (stereo, so 16+17)<br/>- compiled `sw_sampler_fx.scsyndef` lives in `synthesis/synthdefs/`<br/>- SC-side test verifies non-silent output for a known impulse input and frequency-domain check that 61.74 Hz comb peak is present when `comb_b_amount > 0` |\n+| 3 | T-003 | Implement `sampler_dispatch.py` that converts a `(SampleRecord, PerformanceIntent, params)` tuple into the OSC bundle (`/s_new sw_sampler ...` + buffer-pool acquire) and ships it to scsynth. | T1 | 4 | 3 | CCS-012 | — | - `dispatch_sample(record, intent, *, position, position_rate, grain_size_ms, density, pitch_transpose, amp, fx_send) -> SamplerHandle` issues `/b_allocRead` (if needed), `/s_new sw_sampler ...` and returns a handle for later `/n_set gate 0` release<br/>- correlates `record.gain_db` with `amp`<br/>- handles per-mode effects presets (delay_time / verb_mix / freeze / comb_b vary by mode)<br/>- tests with mock OSC client verify correct bundle ordering, gate-release path, and per-mode preset application |\n+| 4 | T-004 | Per-voice gate-controlled lifecycle: composer can `play_sampler(record, duration_sec)` for fire-and-forget OR `start_sampler(record) -> handle; stop_sampler(handle)` for sustained voices. | T1 | 4 | 3 | CCS-013 | — | - `sampler_dispatch.play_sampler(record, duration_sec, **params)` schedules a fire-and-forget grain cloud with an internal envelope of `duration_sec`<br/>- `start_sampler` / `stop_sampler` returns/uses a handle for sustained sampler voices that match the bowed/pad lifecycle<br/>- both code paths feed through the same `dispatch_sample` core<br/>- tests verify both lifecycles and that they can run concurrently without buffer-id collision |\n+| 5 | T-005 | Integrate sampler effects bus into `master_bus.py` mix slot with appropriate gain staging (peak-normalized, not RMS) and post-mix compression bypass to preserve grain transients. | T1 | 4 | 3 | CCS-014 | — | - `master_bus.apply_master_bus_scene` recognizes a `sampler_bus` mix slot with default gain -3 dB (peak-normalized so quieter library samples don't disappear)<br/>- post-mix compression for the sampler slot has `compression_ratio = 1.5` (lower than the 4.0 used elsewhere) so grain transients survive<br/>- tests verify gain staging on a known-amplitude input and grain-transient preservation via peak-vs-RMS ratio |\n+| 6 | T-006 | Implement `sample_capture_daemon.py` rolling 60-second buffers reading from `system:capture_1` (contact mic) and `system:capture_2` (room mic) via JACK. | T1 | 4 | 3 | CCS-015 | — | - daemon opens two JACK ports `cypherclaw-capture:in_contact` and `cypherclaw-capture:in_room`<br/>- each maintains a 60-second numpy ring buffer at 48 kHz<br/>- exposes `get_window(source, duration_sec, offset_sec) -> np.ndarray` for the moment-detector to pull recent windows<br/>- handles JACK xruns gracefully (logs, does not crash)<br/>- tests with a synthetic JACK input fixture verify ring-buffer correctness, window extraction, and xrun recovery |\n+| 7 | T-007 | Implement interesting-moment detector: novelty (spectral flux) + transient density + RMS thresholds + duration-min/max gating. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCS-016 | — | - `sample_capture_daemon.py::InterestingMomentDetector` pulls 1-second windows every 250 ms<br/>- flags a window when: `spectral_flux > 0.6 * recent_median` AND `rms > -45 dBFS` AND `transient_count >= 2` AND `since_last_capture > 30 sec`<br/>- on flag, expands to a 4–8 second window centered on the flagged sub-window (length proportional to spectral richness)<br/>- thresholds are tunable via env / config<br/>- tests with canned audio fixtures (silence, footsteps, dishwasher hum, music) verify expected flag/no-flag for each |\n+| 8 | T-008 | Auto-tag captured samples: arc phase, mood, presence, time-of-day, plus heuristic acoustic tags (warm if low spectral centroid, metallic if high+narrow band, transient if high transient density, etc.). | T1 | 5 | 3 | CCS-017 | — | - `sample_capture_daemon.py::auto_tag(window, context) -> dict` returns a dict mergeable into `SampleRecord`<br/>- arc_phase / mood / presence pulled from `/tmp/organism_state.json` and `/tmp/room_presence.json`<br/>- character tags derived from heuristics: spectral_centroid<800Hz → \"warm\"; narrow-band high-centroid → \"metallic\"; sustained_amplitude_ratio>0.7 → \"sustained\"; transient_density>3/sec → \"percussive\"; pitch_confidence>0.7 → \"harmonic\"; etc.<br/>- tests verify each heuristic against canned fixtures and that the merged record validates against `SampleRecord` schema |\n+| 9 | T-009 | Captured samples land in `samples/contact/` or `samples/room/` as 24-bit 48 kHz WAV with metadata-tagged filename and an entry in `index.sqlite`. | T1 | 4 | 3 | CCS-018 | — | - `sample_capture_daemon.py::save_capture(window, source, tags) -> SampleRecord` writes WAV with filename pattern `<source>_<YYYYMMDDTHHMMSSZ>_<arc>_<sampleid>.wav`<br/>- WAV is 24-bit PCM, 48 kHz, peak-normalized to -1 dBFS unless `peak < -30 dBFS` in which case raw is preserved<br/>- record inserted into `index.sqlite` with `gain_db` set to the normalization adjustment<br/>- tests verify file presence, format (24/48), peak-normalize behavior, and DB row |\n+| 10 | T-010 | Implement self-quotation loop: when a song completes with arc-payoff > threshold AND clicks=0, sample a 4-second window of `SuperCollider:out_1` for the next session. | T1 | 4 | 3 | CCS-019 | — | - `tools/duet_composer.py` post-song hook calls `sample_capture_daemon::self_quote(score_summary)` when arc_payoff > 0.6 AND click_count == 0 AND mode != working_ambience<br/>- daemon captures from `SuperCollider:out_1` (via `system:capture_X` after a small JACK loopback connection it manages itself) the 4-second window centered on the moment of peak rolling_peak during the song<br/>- saves to `samples/self/` with `arc_phase`, `mood`, `mode`, and a `self_quote_source_song_id` extra tag<br/>- tests with a mock self-listener stream and arc-payoff fixture verify trigger condition, capture window, and tag propagation |\n \n **Sprint 1 total:** ~30 hrs\n \n@@ -29,16 +29,11 @@\n \n | Order | Task ID | Description | Tier | Complexity | Est (hrs) | Reqs | Deps | Criteria |\n |-------|---------|-------------|------|------------|-----------|------|------|----------|\n-| 11 | T-011 | Implement R12 Sensor-to-Intent Aggregation Matrix: smoothed IIR + hysteresis → aggregate intentions (global_energy, global_restraint, global_brightness). | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-030 | T-001 | - `render/rules/sensor_intent.py` takes raw SenseWeave sensor stream, applies one-pole IIR smoothing (α≈0.1), threshold with hysteresis, and multiplies by sensor→intention weight matrix<br/>- outputs aggregate_intentions, never direct synth parameters<br/>- listener-reverse-engineer test: given recorded sensor stream and rendered output, no single sensor can be shown to drive any single synth parameter at correlation > 0.85 |\n-| 12 | T-012 | Implement bounded reactive delta track in scheduler with per-parameter modulation caps. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-031 | T-001 | - scheduler writes sensor_tempo_scale ∈ [0.92, 1.08], sensor_amp_scale ∈ [0.80, 1.20], sensor_brightness ∈ [-1.0, +1.0] onto each Event<br/>- delta track is persisted as JSON alongside audio output for replay<br/>- out-of-bounds values clamped and logged<br/>- tests verify clamping, persistence, and replay consumes the delta track |\n-| 13 | T-013 | Expose aggregate-intention telemetry (global_energy/restraint/brightness) in operator diagnostics, never raw one-to-one mappings. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-033 | T-001 | - `operator_diagnostics.py` extended with aggregate_intentions block<br/>- raw sensor values are NOT surfaced alongside synth parameters in diagnostics (prevents accidentally re-introducing gimmicky reverse-mappings)<br/>- tests verify telemetry shape and absence of raw pairings |\n-| 14 | T-014 | Build the metric battery: IOI CoV, velocity σ, DNVR/DNODR, pitch-class entropy H1, Grooving Similarity (GS), tempo autocorrelation ρ₁, LZ76 compression ratio, novelty peaks per phrase, silence-at-phrase-boundaries. | T1 | 5 | 3 | CCH-034 | T-001 | - `render/metrics.py` computes each metric on PerformedPart<br/>- tooling: partitura for score I/O, mir_eval for segmentation, MusDr/MusPy for symbolic metrics, librosa for audio-rendered SSM + Foote novelty, madmom for beat/tempo cross-check<br/>- documented pass bands from the research: IOI CoV 0.04–0.12, velocity σ 12–22, DNVR 0.25–0.7, pitch H1 2.3–3.0, GS 0.6–0.9, tempo ρ₁ 0.7–0.95, LZ76 0.4–0.7, ≥1 novelty peak per phrase, ≥100 ms silence at phrase boundaries<br/>- tests run metrics on rule-disabled flat-line control (should fail pass bands) and full-stack render (should pass) |\n-| 15 | T-015 | Build anti-pattern tests: quantization ghosting, dynamic compression, motif ossification, random-as-expression (Ljung-Box), symmetric-arc uncanny, dead-silence failure. | T1 | 6 | 3 | CCH-035 | T-001 | - `render/antipatterns.py` implements each detector<br/>- quantization ghosting: velocity σ > 0 AND timing σ < 3 ms → fail<br/>- dynamic compression: velocity range < 20 → fail<br/>- motif ossification: GS > 0.95 across repeated sections → fail<br/>- random-as-expression: Ljung-Box fails to reject white noise on tempo or velocity series → fail<br/>- symmetric-arc uncanny: per-phrase worm convex-hull shape variance < 5% across phrases → fail<br/>- dead-silence failure: no rests ≥200 ms in a 2-minute melodic passage → fail<br/>- each detector has a positive fixture (should fail) and negative fixture (should pass) |\n-| 16 | T-016 | Implement performance-worm logger: 2D trajectory in tempo–loudness space + convex-hull area computation as CI artifact. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-036 | T-001 | - `render/worm.py` emits per-piece worm JSON and PNG to `artifacts/worms/<piece_id>/`<br/>- convex-hull area computed via scipy.spatial.ConvexHull<br/>- reject point-worm (mechanical: area < 1.0) and space-filling worm (random: area > saturation threshold)<br/>- CI attaches worm PNGs to build artifacts for listener review |\n-| 17 | T-017 | Integrate metric battery + anti-pattern detectors into CI gate with fail-on-regression policy. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-037 | T-001 | - pytest gate runs metrics on a curated fixture set of 5-minute rendered pieces<br/>- any metric outside pass band or any anti-pattern trigger fails the build<br/>- pass bands are per-intent-tag where applicable (withhold-tagged phrases allow lower velocity σ)<br/>- tests verify a deliberately broken render fails the gate and a healthy render passes |\n-| 18 | T-018 | Embed rule-stack provenance in exported audio metadata (e.g., WAV iXML chunk or sidecar JSON) for listener-review workflow. | T1 | 4 | 3 | CCH-039 | T-001 | - each rendered audio file gets a `.render.json` sidecar with Event list, rule_stack per event, PerformanceIntent per phrase, SectionEnvelope per section, seeds, delta_track path<br/>- format documented in `my-claw/docs/render-audio-sidecar.md`<br/>- tests verify sidecar presence, schema, and ability to replay from sidecar alone |\n+| 11 | T-011 | Implement anti-pattern detectors: `sampler_dominating` (sampler event count > 0.6 × total events) and `sampler_silent_quintet_member` (sampler used in <5% of last 50 pieces, mode-weighted). | T1 | 7 | 3 | CCS-030 | T-001 | - integrated into `render/antipatterns.py` (CCH-015)<br/>- `sampler_dominating` fires per-piece, surfaces in metrics gate as warning (downgrade to MUST FIX after 3 consecutive)<br/>- `sampler_silent_quintet_member` fires across rolling window of last 50 pieces; mode-weighted means the threshold scales with `sampler_density` per mode (so working_ambience never trips it)<br/>- tests verify each detector with synthetic piece histories |\n+| 12 | T-012 | End-to-end smoke test on cypherclaw: capture a known room sound, watch the composer self-quote it within 3 pieces, verify the self-listener observes the resulting peaks. | T1 | 4 | 3 | CCS-031 | T-001 | - `my-claw/tests/test_sampler_e2e.py` (skipped on CI, runs on cypherclaw via `pytest -m cypherclaw_e2e`)<br/>- plays a 4-second sine sweep through the speakers, lets contact/room mic capture it, waits for the daemon to detect+tag, forces the composer to compose 3 short pieces, asserts at least one of them dispatched a sampler with the captured sample<br/>- self-listener observes nonzero peak in the expected scene<br/>- documented in `docs/sampler-smoke-test.md` |\n+| 13 | T-013 | Update `docs/cypherclaw-musicianship-roadmap.md` to reflect the quintet, document the sampler architecture in `docs/cypherclaw-sampler-architecture.md`, and add a one-page artistic-intent doc `docs/cypherclaw-sampler-artistic-intent.md`. | T2 | 5 | 6 | CCS-033 | T-001 | - musicianship roadmap mentions the quintet and sampler-as-memory<br/>- architecture doc covers the data model, daemon, dispatch, effects bus, and selector<br/>- artistic-intent doc captures the three usages (memory of place, self-quotation, found library) and the five principles<br/>- docs link from each other; mkdocs / repo nav updated if applicable |\n \n-**Sprint 2 total:** ~24 hrs\n+**Sprint 2 total:** ~12 hrs\n \n ---\n \n@@ -46,18 +41,18 @@\n \n | Order | Task ID | Description | Tier | Complexity | Est (hrs) | Reqs | Deps | Criteria |\n |-------|---------|-------------|------|------------|-----------|------|------|----------|\n-| 19 | T-019 | Enforce role-filter gating across R1–R8 with a single shared contract; verify machine identity preservation end-to-end. | T1 | 7 | 3 | CCH-020 | T-011 | - all R1–R8 rules check `rule.applies_to(event.role)` before mutating the event<br/>- integration test: ostinato + melody passage renders with melody shaped and ostinato exactly quantized<br/>- gate test: passage where ostinato has non-zero timing_deviation_ms fails (indicates a rule leaked) |\n-| 20 | T-020 | Integrate partitura for phrase-feature extraction: harmonic_charge, melodic_charge, metric_weight, cadential detection, contour apex. | T1 | 3 | 3 | CCH-021 | T-011 | - `render/features.py` wraps partitura load_score + per-phrase feature computation<br/>- features annotated onto Events during 