sdp/verification/t-022@20260425t183959zc-verify.md:11:{"type":"message","timestamp":"2026-04-26T04:44:58.066Z","role":"user","content":"# Verification: Task T-022@20260425T183959Zc\n\n**Task:** Wire post-piece hook that consumes tracker state, derives arc-payoff summary, and writes journal entry to storage. Tests for hook invocation and file output.\n**Tier:** T1\n\nYou are the VERIFY agent for this task. The LEAD agent has completed their work.\n\n\n## Review Checklist\n\n1. **Review recent commits:**\n   ```bash\n   git log --oneline -5\n   git diff HEAD~3 --stat\n   ```\n\n2. **Review code changes:**\n   ```bash\n   git diff HEAD~3\n   ```\n\n4. **Check ESCALATIONS.md** for any flagged issues.\n\n5. **Run the test suite:**\n   ```bash\n   pip install -e '.[dev]' && pytest tests/ -x\n   ```\n\n## Evaluation Criteria\n\nEvaluate the work against these five dimensions:\n\n1. **Correctness**: Does the output match the requirements/spec?\n2. **Completeness**: Are there gaps, missing edge cases, or unhandled scenarios?\n3. **Consistency**: Does the output follow established patterns and conventions?\n4. **Security**: Are there vulnerabilities, leaked secrets, or unsafe practices?\n5. **Quality**: Does the output meet the quality gates for this phase?\n\n## Output\n\nWrite your verification report and all findings to this exact path:\n`sdp/verification/t-022@20260425t183959zc-verify.md`\nDo not use a different filename or directory.\n\nUse this format:\n\n```markdown\n# Verification Report — T-022@20260425T183959Zc\n\n**Verify Agent:** [your agent name]\n**Date:** [today]\n**Artifacts Reviewed:** [list files reviewed]\n\n## Correctness\n[assessment]\n\n## Completeness\n[assessment]\n\n## Consistency\n[assessment]\n\n## Security\n[assessment]\n\n## Quality\n[assessment]\n\n## Issues Found\n- [ ] [Issue — severity: blocking/minor]\n\n## Verdict: [PASS | PASS WITH NOTES | FAIL]\n\n## Notes for Lead Agent\n[specific items to address]\n```\n\nCommit the verification report.\n\n## Candidate Hardening (Auto-Generated)\n\nUse the recurring failure patterns below as mandatory hardening checks:\n- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: Runtime does not invoke bootstrap_identity on startup, so the identity file is never guaranteed to be created automatically at first run. Severity: blocking.\n- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: Add bootstrap_identity() invocation in startup flow (before FirstBootAnnouncer) so first boots mint and persist identity automatically..\n- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: Ensure this path is used on both standalone and federated modes..\n- Enforce behavioral regression tests before completion: Add an integration test that exercises startup and verifies identity persistence between boots..\n- Enforce behavioral regression tests before completion: Re-run pip install -e '.[dev]' && pytest tests/ -x after wiring the startup path..\n"}
sdp/verification/t-022@20260425t183959zc-verify.md:20:{"type":"tool_result","timestamp":"2026-04-26T04:45:06.028Z","tool_id":"run_shell_command_1777178705833_0","status":"success","output":"commit 0345b299714d30cb3f1f7c480fa9eb4edccad83d (HEAD -> feat/graceful-degradation)\nAuthor: Anthony Ainsworth <anthony@cascadiantech.com>\nDate:   Sat Apr 25 21:44:14 2026 -0700\n\n    feat(sampler): add post-piece hook that writes usage journal entries [T-022@20260425T183959Zc]\n    \n    Adds `post_piece_hook(tracker, arc_payoff_score, journal_path)` and\n    `derive_arc_payoff_summary(...)` to `senseweave.usage_journal`. The hook\n    consumes the active `SampleUsageTracker`, derives a banded textual\n    arc-payoff summary (weak/moderate/strong + score + sample count), folds\n    the accumulated plays into a `JournalEntry`, and appends it to the\n    journal file. Tests cover summary banding, hook invocation + on-disk\n    output, multi-piece appends, and the no-active-piece error path.\n    \n    Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.7 <noreply@anthropic.com>\n\ndiff --git a/my-claw/tools/senseweave/usage_journal.py b/my-claw/tools/senseweave/usage_journal.py\nindex 2418521..52eed3c 100644\n--- a/my-claw/tools/senseweave/usage_journal.py\n+++ b/my-claw/tools/senseweave/usage_journal.py\n@@ -114,3 +114,40 @@ class SampleUsageTracker:\n         self.timestamp = None\n         self.samples_played = []\n         return entry\n+\n+\n+def derive_arc_payoff_summary(*, arc_payoff_score: float, sample_count: int) -> str:\n+    \"\"\"Render a short textual summary from a numeric arc-payoff score and\n+    the number of samples that played in the piece.\"\"\"\n+    if arc_payoff_score >= 0.6:\n+        band = \"strong\"\n+    elif arc_payoff_score >= 0.3:\n+        band = \"moderate\"\n+    else:\n+        band = \"weak\"\n+    return f\"{band} payoff (score={arc_payoff_score:.2f}) over {sample_count} sample(s)\"\n+\n+\n+def post_piece_hook(\n+    tracker: SampleUsageTracker,\n+    *,\n+    arc_payoff_score: float,\n+    journal_path: Path = JOURNAL_PATH,\n+) -> JournalEntry:\n+    \"\"\"Composer post-piece hook: consumes ``tracker`` state, derives an\n+    arc-payoff summary from ``arc_payoff_score``, folds the accumulated\n+    plays into a :class:`JournalEntry` (resetting the tracker), and\n+    appends the entry to ``journal_path``.\n+\n+    Returns the appended ``JournalEntry`` so callers can log or inspect\n+    it. Raises ``RuntimeError`` (via ``finish_piece``) if the tracker\n+    has no active piece.\n+    \"\"\"\n+    sample_count = len(tracker.samples_played)\n+    summary = derive_arc_payoff_summary(\n+        arc_payoff_score=arc_payoff_score,\n+        sample_count=sample_count,\n+    )\n+    entry = tracker.finish_piece(arc_payoff=summary)\n+    append_to_journal(entry, path=journal_path)\n+    return entry\ndiff --git a/tests/test_usage_journal.py b/tests/test_usage_journal.py\nindex 70154a2..0bf2da7 100644\n--- a/tests/test_usage_journal.py\n+++ b/tests/test_usage_journal.py\n@@ -11,6 +11,8 @@ from senseweave.usage_journal import (\n     SamplePlay,\n     SampleUsageTracker,\n     append_to_journal,\n+    derive_arc_payoff_summary,\n+    post_piece_hook,\n     read_journal,\n )\n \n@@ -277,3 +279,87 @@ def test_tracker_entry_round_trips_through_journal(tmp_path):\n     assert [sp.sample_id for sp in restored.samples_played] == [\"kick\", \"snare\"]\n     assert restored.samples_played[1].transposition == -1\n     assert restored.samples_played[1].fx_preset == \"reverb\"\n+\n+\n+def test_derive_arc_payoff_summary_bands():\n+    assert derive_arc_payoff_summary(arc_payoff_score=0.0, sample_count=0).startswith(\"weak\")\n+    assert derive_arc_payoff_summary(arc_payoff_score=0.29, sample_count=2).startswith(\"weak\")\n+    assert derive_arc_payoff_summary(arc_payoff_score=0.3, sample_count=2).startswith(\"moderate\")\n+    assert derive_arc_payoff_summary(arc_payoff_score=0.59, sample_count=4).startswith(\"moderate\")\n+    assert derive_arc_payoff_summary(arc_payoff_score=0.6, sample_count=4).startswith(\"strong\")\n+    assert derive_arc_payoff_summary(arc_payoff_score=1.0, sample_count=7).startswith(\"strong\")\n+    summary = derive_arc_payoff_summary(arc_payoff_score=0.42, sample_count=3)\n+    assert \"0.42\" in summary\n+    assert \"3 sample\" in summary\n+\n+\n+def test_post_piece_hook_writes_journal_entry(tmp_path):\n+    journal_path = tmp_path / \"usage_journal.jsonl\"\n+    tracker = SampleUsageTracker()\n+    tracker.start_piece(piece_id=\"piece-hook\", timestamp=\"2026-04-25T19:20:00Z\")\n+    tracker.record_play(\n+        sample_id=\"bd\",\n+        source=\"kick_pack\",\n+        transposition=0,\n+        fx_preset=\"punchy\",\n+        played_at_row=0,\n+    )\n+    tracker.record_play(\n+        sample_id=\"sn\",\n+        source=\"snare_pack\",\n+        transposition=-2,\n+        fx_preset=\"reverb\",\n+        played_at_row=4,\n+    )\n+\n+    entry = post_piece_hook(\n+        tracker,\n+        arc_payoff_score=0.75,\n+        journal_path=journal_path,\n+    )\n+\n+    assert isinstance(entry, JournalEntry)\n+    assert entry.piece_id == \"piece-hook\"\n+    assert [sp.sample_id for sp in entry.samples_played] == [\"bd\", \"sn\"]\n+    assert entry.arc_payoff.startswith(\"strong\")\n+    assert \"0.75\" in entry.arc_payoff\n+    assert \"2 sample\" in entry.arc_payoff\n+\n+    # Tracker is reset after hook runs.\n+    assert not tracker.is_active\n+    assert tracker.samples_played == []\n+\n+    # Entry was actually written to disk.\n+    on_disk = read_journal(path=journal_path)\n+    assert len(on_disk) == 1\n+    assert on_disk[0].piece_id == \"piece-hook\"\n+    assert on_disk[0].arc_payoff == entry.arc_payoff\n+    assert [sp.sample_id for sp in on_disk[0].samples_played] == [\"bd\", \"sn\"]\n+\n+\n+def test_post_piece_hook_appends_across_pieces(tmp_path):\n+    journal_path = tmp_path / \"usage_journal.jsonl\"\n+    tracker = SampleUsageTracker()\n+\n+    tracker.start_piece(piece_id=\"piece-1\", timestamp=\"2026-04-25T19:21:00Z\")\n+    tracker.record_play(\n+        sample_id=\"a\", source=\"src\", transposition=0, fx_preset=\"dry\", played_at_row=0,\n+    )\n+    post_piece_hook(tracker, arc_payoff_score=0.1, journal_path=journal_path)\n+\n+    tracker.start_piece(piece_id=\"piece-2\", timestamp=\"2026-04-25T19:22:00Z\")\n+    post_piece_hook(tracker, arc_payoff_score=0.9, journal_path=journal_path)\n+\n+    entries = read_journal(path=journal_path)\n+    assert [e.piece_id for e in entries] == [\"piece-1\", \"piece-2\"]\n+    assert entries[0].arc_payoff.startswith(\"weak\")\n+    assert entries[1].arc_payoff.startswith(\"strong\")\n+    assert len(entries[1].samples_played) == 0\n+\n+\n+def test_post_piece_hook_without_active_piece_raises(tmp_path):\n+    journal_path = tmp_path / \"usage_journal.jsonl\"\n+    tracker = SampleUsageTracker()\n+    with pytest.raises(RuntimeError):\n+        post_piece_hook(tracker, arc_payoff_score=0.5, journal_path=journal_path)\n+    assert not journal_path.exists()"}
